text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
cerita hidup¬†jang ja yeon¬†tak hanya sampai di situ saja, beberapa temuan ini membuat banyak orang miris. apa sajakah itu?

kehilangan orangtua
pada 1999 silam, hidup jang jo yeon mulai seperti mimpi buruk saat orangtuanya meninggal dalam sebuah kecelakaan. sejak itu, ia tinggal bersama kakak dan adik laki-lakinya.

secara tidak langsung, jang jo yeon merasa bertanggung jawab menghidupi saudara-saudaranya. namun, kabar ini belum mendapatkan konfirmasi dari pihak keluarganya.

debut
pada 2006, jang jo yeon debut di industri hiburan sebagai model iklan. baru pada 2009, namanya melejit sejak sukses berperan sebagai salah satu karakter antagonis di drama¬†boys over flowers¬†bersama ku hye sun dan lee min ho.
sejak saat itu, nama jang jo yeon pun mendapatkan tawaran dari berbagai acara hingga berakting di film lain. saat ditemukan gantung diri pada 2009 silam, jang jo yeon tengah menanti film barunya rilis,¬†where is jung seung pil.

depresi
industri hiburan membuat sang artis mengalami depresi. ia harus melayani 31 pria, diperkirakan berasal dari kalangan petinggi dan pejabat di industri hiburan, total sebanyak 100 kali.

hal itu membuat depresi yang dialaminya makin parah. ia pun sempat mendapatkan perawatan untuk menghilangkan depresi yang dideritanya, dilansir dari¬†naver.

skandal besar
jang ja yeon menyimpan semua catatan dan bukti pria yang minta ditemaninya. sebuah skandal besar akan terkuak, beberapa orang ini dikabarkan memiliki posisi penting di korea selatan, seperti pejabat pemerintah, produser, dan bos-bos media terlibat, diwartakanallkpop.

polisi yang sedang menyelidiki kasus jang ja yeon tahu fakta ini, tetapi memilih untuk mengabaikannya. setelah gerakan #metoo, melawan tindakan pelecehan atau kekerasan seksual merajalela di korea selatan, kasus jang jo yeon akhirnya kembali dibuka setelah 9 tahun berlalu, dilansir dari¬†koreaboo.

text:
i have endured racial segregation, childhood trauma, rape, homelessness, sexual assualt and racism. i have survived 4 mental illnesses, bullying,  a spouse going to jail for domestic abuse, 8 suicide attempts, 6 psych admissions, drug addiction and self harm. i pushed through the death of my grandmother, and  my partner having a brain injury which required round the clock hospital care after a near fatal car crash.  i have stolen, been divorced twice, i have lied, been arrested, gotten a dui, ran away, and i've hurt many people and made many mistakes along the way. these are my "sins" and i lay them down before all. as i wake up on the day of my birth knowing and affirming my journey and growth i affirm that  i am not the things my family did. i am not the voices in my head. i am not the pieces of the broken things inside.i am light. i am light. i am not the  mistakes i have made or any other things that cause me pain. i am not the pieces of the dreams i've left behind. i am light. today i honor this day of my birth and honor my 35 years on this planet in this galaxy. i honor my wholeness with all i've been through because i value me and my time. i could have easily cost myself my own life decades ago but i fought for everything. i fought for life because i am divinity defined. i am the god on the inside. i am light and as i burn candles in honor of life i smile because this birthday means everything to me.  i am concious and i rise above pain and suffering. i understand that i am not the color of my eyes, i am not the skin on the outside. i am not my sexual orientation, i am not my age, my race, my soul inside is all light. i am not my mental illness, i am neither black or white. i am not a man or a woman. i am a star, a piece of it all; i am light. knowing this i thank you universe for your blessings. your guidance is wise indeed. thank you for your blessings. your lessons live on in me. thank you thank you thank you. thank you thank you.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‚Äòugh. totally ugly‚Äô to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it‚Äôs worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don‚Äôt necessarily know it‚Äôs being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it‚Äôs worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you‚Äôre doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people‚Äôs personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn‚Äôt have seen, and couldn‚Äôt have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, ‚Äúwould work for anyone‚Äù. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they‚Äôre mercenaries. they‚Äôll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it‚Äôs an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing ‚Äì at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public ‚Äì our intimate family connections, our ‚Äúlikes‚Äù, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that‚Äôs expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn‚Äôs don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica‚Äôs parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan‚Äôs app may not have been completely deleted. kogan‚Äôs app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

your friendly reminder of just exactly who‚Äôs to blame for shutting down our government. [man, i‚Äôm getting tired of posting these‚Ä¶]
day 21‚Ä¶ you did it donald #trump! after already blowing by the [one and only] shutdown under #obama, you‚Äôve tied the record for longest government shutdown ‚Äî equalling the 21 day shutdown under bill clinton.
from here on out, just as it‚Äôs been for this entire shutdown from the minute you offered to ‚Äútake the mantle‚Äù on december 11, 2018 ‚Äî it‚Äôs all about you!
800,000+ federal workers are now going without paychecks [including some legally required to still work] and countless other americans are feeling the residual effects of this dumb #trumpshutdown. 
out of touch and just plain cruel.
but, why exactly is our government shutdown over american taxpayers paying for the wall ‚Äî when #mexico is supposed to be paying for the wall? 
i don't give a crap about his fan‚Äôs spins and interpretations of what he meant to say, or what he really means‚Ä¶ he said:
"i will build a great wall -- and nobody builds walls better than me, believe me --and i'll build them very inexpensively. i will build a great, great wall on our southern border, and i will make mexico pay for that wall. mark my words."
words‚Ä¶ marked.
he was very clear and specific. he even put it in writing!
he wants money for his stupid wall?‚Ä¶ it's going to have to be in pesos‚Ä¶ >>>end of discussion.
the #democrats now have control of the house and will put forth sensible legislation to benefit the people of this country. and, for the first time, hold #trump to account‚Ä¶ his life will now become a virtual and perpetual deep colonoscopy‚Ä¶ 
the saudis. abuse of power. corruption. ethics. kavanaugh. tax returns. #russia. obstruction of justice! you name it‚Ä¶ we'll really start getting to the bottom of it‚Ä¶all! 
to save #america we must hold to account the inept, corrupt and amoral unindicted co-conspirator in the oval office: #illegitimate #failingpresident#donaldtrump.

text:
aujourdhui, jai appris la lecon la plus importante de toute ma vie. jai appris que pour ce delivrer dune souffrance il fallait accepter de la vivre. pour qu'un cercle vicieux cesse, il faut en parler et comprendre d'ou sa vient. j'ai compris. garder un secret aussi lourd peut affecter tellement de chose dans la vie d'une personne... pour ma part ca affecter toutes mes relations amoureuses ou mes frequentations. des que je rencontre quelqu'un de bien qui pourrait m'aimer ou m'apprecie, je m'auto sabote! en faisant en sorte que cette personne me laisse, qu'il me trouve assez gossante, afin qu'il parte et que je n'aille pas a me laisser aimer ou apprecier comme il faut, surement parce que j'ai l'impression que je merite juste ce que lui m'avait fait subir, il y a de cela 5 ans maintenant, que je ne merite pas qu'on me traite bien. le mot non il ne connaissait pas, ca ne faisait pas partie de son vocabulaire j'imagine... aujourd'hui, j'ai decid√© de me lib√©rer afin de ne plus trainer ca avec moi en 2019, de lui pardonner de m'avoir fait ca et de me pardonner a moi de l'avoir laisser faire. si je vous le partage c'est parce que je me suis rendue compte que je commence encore a m'auto saboter dans une relation que j'apprecie tel quelle est, parfaite dans ses imperfections, je m'excuse sincerement, pour tout, cette relation me tient a coeur, cest pourquoi jai decider de faire cesser ce cercle vicieux qui fait partie de ma vie. je suis tann√©e et je sais que malgrer ma peur de partagee sa avec vous c'est ce que sa prenait pour me liberer de ce fardeau qui me hante... tres peu de gens le savent. je veux vous dire, que cest important de se respecter, d'accepter qui on est, de faire comprendre que non cest non peu importe comment tu t'habilles et s'il t'aime, alors il devrait te respecter. tu ne devrais jamais te sentir obliger de faire des choses que tu ne veux pas. le harcelement sexuelle cest la pire chose, sa affecte. n'ayez jamais honte d'en parler parce que la seule personne qui doit avoir honte cest celle qui agis comme ca. liberez vous des souffrances qui vous habitent et surtout respecter vos limites. je vous aime ‚ô•Ô∏è #metoo #neverlookback
encore merci @jeremydemay2

text:
these past few years are hard for sexual assault survivors because you can't turn on the tv, open a paper, or listen to the radio without hearing about it. then you see other victims getting support and affirmation in their communities while you are ignored in your own or condemned.  it makes you feel worthless and like you deserved it.

text:
when the media (and its emotionally unstable cousin social media) doesn't get it, random huffpo headlines

this week sees two more blacklisting witch hunts:  r kelly and kevin hart.  both assassinated deliberately by biased media.  ben lee reminds me of when gay "activists" (emotionally unstable 4th grade reading level social media) decided a firefox executive who donated to the california mormon prop 8 needed to be "punished" for practicing his legal rights as a citizen of the us, donating funds to a political campaign he supported.  the gay "activists" got the "criminal" fired for lawfully engaging in democracy.

now picture that situation occurring in 1992, only the exec was gay and had donated to a proposition for increased funding for aids research?  and the straight people tried to get him fired?  hate crime in reverse.

apparently, kevin hart is not allowed to share his life experience as a black son and a black father, and speak to his audience about his feelings about possibly having a gay son?  the ambush was planned on, and aimed at the wishy washy academy, already punch drunk from #oscarssowhite, #metoo. 
it isn't ben lee's place to censor an honest conversation within kevin hart's community about being gay. laughter opens wounds and disinfects them.  the plots of will ferrell movies should not be used to attack a man's worth to his audience, other than ferrell's, perhaps.  lee  is a pretentious spoiled leftie wanker at the guardian who lives in london, who cares about his political correctness?  how safe his life is, inside the soft bubble up until brexit.

he created this incident for his own pr stunt in cynical career planning.  what right did he have to collect all these assorted statements and demand an oscar-related apology?  he isn't the academy.

now, a salacious tv show selling kinky sex for ratings had a very good week pushing r kelly's sex life.  and now he too is to be erased from the public record? like mario batali?  without even a serious journalist investigating?  wtf? 
this "deleted from digital" is a little too chapelle show and we all know what happened to dave.  the historical record is, like, the historical record.

text:
it‚Äôs duck face / butt face day! 
duck face/butt face is one of the many things i don‚Äôt love about social media.

so it‚Äôs time to break that belief and try that for my #sharingshame challenge.

at first i thought i didn‚Äôt love duck face/butt face because it was egotistical or vain, but then i decided why shouldn‚Äôt people flaunt themselves and their beauty. 
we are all beautiful, why should we be ashamed of how we look.

but then....i decided that selfie and particularly butt face/ duck face - was inauthentic and that‚Äôs why i didn‚Äôt like it. 
it was copying everyone else and it certainly wasn‚Äôt a true representation of how you are feeling, so therefore i wouldn‚Äôt do that. 
i wouldn‚Äôt do it because: * it might make someone think i am vain or think a lot of myself
* it might make someone else feel less than me
* it might make someone judge their own day and wonder why they couldn‚Äôt feel that way
* it was fake, i didn‚Äôt just feel sexy
* someone might judge me and think i‚Äôm not beautiful enough to do a selfie
* i‚Äôm not <insert celeb name here> so i‚Äôm not pretty enough to do it * i don‚Äôt need to take selfies to feel good about myself 
blah. blah. blah ü§Ø

i was ok to do duck face with a group of friends (for fun) but never alone and taking a selfie of myself alone was cringeworthy, particularly in public. 
so today i am trying it on for size, shameless beauty pics. 
i‚Äôm hoping by the end of this challenge, i feel comfortable enough to share my outfit or take a selfie without that cringe feeling!

if you want to join me on the #sharingshame challenge. 
try taking a selfie that you feel you really couldn‚Äôt do. 
just try it on for size and see what happens. 
you butt is worth it üèÜ

text:
your touch. your mistakes. my blood. 
just in case you can‚Äôt read my bad handwriting,
because you invaded my bones and took what wasn‚Äôt yours to take. my skin riddled against your touch, my soul broken from your mistakes. you drowned me in my tears, tore me wide apart and lost me in my blood. now i‚Äôm fighting a war with myself when you sent me to battle. so i fish for ways to banish the thoughts within, nothing good nothing kind, and i‚Äôve longed to rip them off my skin. my fate now an impossibility, tightly packaged dashing down, hardly making many sound. hmmm his world has become a place where i can‚Äôt bear to sit with myself, and that space, it cannot be -invaded. 
#metoo #metoomovement #writersofinstagram #lamepoetry #poetry #depressionquotes #depressionedits #depressionsupport

text:
#teavwatcherz - here‚Äôs what happened when the police üëÆ üëÆüèΩüëÆüèªüëÆüèøüëÆüèº dropped by read article here via tmz üìç r. kelly came face-to-face with cops in chicago after an anonymous caller claimed the singer was holding two women hostage.

the cook county state attorney's office got a tip friday that kelly was at his trump tower residence with the women ... and he was holding them against their will. we're told cops raced to the property and made contact with r. kelly and the women.

our sources say 5 officers came to the home and ordered kelly into the other room while they questioned the women. according to chicago pd, both women said they were at the residence voluntarily and nothing untoward was going on. police then left without incident. 
we're told the 2 women were joycelyn savage and azriel clary, both of whom have maintained they were with r. kelly voluntarily, despite their parents' strong claims they were the victims of brainwashing.
tmz broke the story ... cops were called to a chicago club thursday morning after a tip was called in that kelly was at the club partying and there was a warrant out for his arrest. officers spoke with kelly -- determined there was no warrant -- and let the singer continue to party. as we reported ... cook county state attorney kimberly foxx has publicly urged victims of kelly to come forward. we're told the victim hotline has been burning up ever since.

i realllllly wanted to spend some time talking about ‚Äúprivilege‚Äù. amplified by social media, ‚Äúprivilege‚Äù has become a normalized aspect of our everyday social justice rhetoric. but what does it really to mean to check your privilege? how can we use it to encourage people to change their behaviors?‚Å£
‚Å£
‚Äúprivilege‚Äù is unearned systematic power and advantages that are granted to a group and those who belong to that group. an in-depth analysis of our privileges can lead to a profound understanding of how our unearned positions in society can contribute to the oppression of others. ‚Å£
‚Å£
but, i think we‚Äôve done a really great job at weaponizing the word ‚Äúprivilege.‚Äù rather than beginning to think about how we can relinquish and share our societal power, the word ‚Äúprivilege‚Äù now causes a lot of folks to shut down. but here‚Äôs how we can recontextualize our arguments about privilege: stop saying ‚Äúprivilege‚Äù so damn much.‚Å£
‚Å£
it‚Äôs not easy, but because privilege comes in so many different forms, it‚Äôs still possible to challenge someone to think about or talk their privileges. to make this easier, ask yourself these questions and answer them in the comments below ‚§µÔ∏è:‚Å£
‚Å£
1. what privileges do i have?‚Å£
‚Å£
2. how do i exert that privilege in the different environments that i‚Äôm in? ‚Å£
‚Å£
3. how can i negatively impact the people around me?‚Å£
‚Å£
4. what are ways in which i can share that power with others?‚Å£ ‚¨áÔ∏è‚¨áÔ∏è‚¨áÔ∏è
‚Å£
then, when talking to others, ask yourself the same questions about the actions of other people. it will be easier to recontextualize the argument without weaponizing ‚Äúprivilege‚Äù.‚Å£

text:
soooo.... i waited before i posted something about #rkelly.  i wanted to take time to process my own thoughts and feelings as a survivor of sexual trauma, and as an advocate who has worked with victims of child sexual abuse, rape, domestic violence, human trafficking..etc.  here are some important issues i want to address.
.
.
looking for support?
 national hotline for sexual assault: 800.656.hope (4673)
in florida? reach out to @fcasv
.
.
 want to hear more about my personal healing journey? join #thebutterflymovement2019 !  it is a cool project i created to empower survivors. includes: an online video bible study, a 1-on-1 photo shoot for each participant and a "butterfly banquet" to celebrate. offered all year!
.
.
 it's not too late to join the jan-march session. you can join up until feb 20th. use promo code early1 $5 off. <link in bio>
.
.

fixed it. to be clear, a young teenager is a girl. please stop letting the experiences of black girls be misconstrued by the centuries-old refusal to let us have our childhoods; stop making us adults earlier so our trauma can be dismissed as voluntary, so our victimization can be conveniently converted into immorality & criminality; so child abuse & pedophilia are easier to excuse, whether by the slavemasters of the past, or the r&b stars of the present. thx #dreamhampton for the courageous @lifetimetv docuseries #survivingrkelly, & pls everyone read the incisive @nytimes piece by @salamishah & @sherphotographs reminding us about the sobering reality that black girls‚Äô truths have historically been invalidated & ignored precisely because they are at the intersection of racial, sexual, & class oppression. no more. huge thx also to @kimberlecrenshaw for coining the term #intersectionality long before it became a hashtag, & shoutout (or ululation out) to @taranajaneen for not only coining #metoo, but powerfully reclaiming it when others would have co-opted its origins, & now officially being the @metoomvmt ceo üí• üñ§ üôèüèΩ
